The hungry waves devour The seaman, young and old drop hour by hour, No single head is spared by ruthless Proserpine.

Me, too, the headlong gust‚ That dogs Orion, ’neath the billows thrust. But, prithee, seamen, shed On my unburied head And limbs with gentle hand some grains of drifting dust Ξ So may the storm that threats the western deep Turn all its wrath away, To smite the forests of Venusia, And thou thy course secure o'er the mild ocean keep!
